channel.title: Anti-leech Concept
channel.description:
This is an anti-leech concept I've had in my head for a while now and one that I was finally able to make and share.
There are no executables in this. Run in eclipse - no bat or sh files.
[url=http://www.mediafire.com/download/8i2eu818nua7hch/AntiLeech.zip]http://www.mediafire.com/download/8i2eu818nua7hch/AntiLeech.zip[/url]
Tell me what you think and read the README.txt. Feel free to expand on this or make it more complicated.

item.title: Anti-leech Concept
item.dc:creator: @Bellend Bellend
item.description:
@Bellend wrote:

If you want credit for your server, why not just override a class that’s necessary for the server to function but no server would need to edit, add some GDI text to the frame with the credits of the original creator, compile the class and delete the source on the release.

That way the only way to remove the credits is to delete a file that is dependant by the client/server and the server/client wont run without it therefore making it permanent and “technically” un-removable unless you know exactly what dependant code is missing.

Thats the way i would do it if i ever released anything.

Read full topic
